## Dogfood (2026-07-14)
After B089 landed on master (`hark start`/`stop`/`restart`), the PATH install
(`uv tool` → `~/.local/bin/hark`, reported as v0.1.0) still rejected `start`
as an invalid choice. Repo venv / `uv run hark` had the commands.

## Expected
Dogfooding master features works from the same `hark` on PATH, or doctor clearly
warns that the tool install is behind git HEAD / package version.

## Actual
Silent lag: agents call `hark start` and fail; ambient was restarted via ad-hoc
pkill instead.

## Ideas
- `hark doctor` compare installed version / git describe / entrypoints
- Document `uv tool install -e .` as the dogfood path in SETUP / skill
- Related historical: B078 (stale arm-cue install)